2023-24 NCAA DI Rankings

Apr 3, 2023 by Jon Kozak

125 - Anthony Noto

Jakob Camacho jumps up to the #3 spot after he defeated Matt Ramos at the Journeymen Collegiate Classic. 

Eddie Ventresca falls to the #18 spot after dropping matches to both Brendan McCrone and Jack Maida. Ventresca's wins last year over Killian Cardinale, Eric Barnett, and Patrick McKee keep him from dropping further. 

McCrone comes into the rankings at the #27 spot for his win over Ventresca. McCrone's win over Tristan Lujan was the biggest of his career, however, McCrone's losses this year to unranked Tristan Lujan and #21 Nick Babin  keep him from climbing higher in the rankings. 

Dominic Mendez comes into the rankings at #29 for defeating Maryland's Braxton Brown. 

Do you have questions or comments for the rankers? We welcome and encourage your feedback. Hit up Jon Kozak (email: Jonathan.Kozak@flosports.tv; Twitter: @KozakJon) and JD Rader (email: jd.rader@flosports.tv; Twitter: @rader_jd).
